        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 10:32AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1032 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Whiteville, or near Bolivar, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Laconia, Medon, Cedar Chapel, Vildo, Middleburg, Hickory Valley,
Hatchie, Chickasaw State Forest, Uptonville, Silerton, Deanburg,
Teague, Cloverport, Whiteville, Bolivar, Toone, Denmark, Leighton,
Van Buren, and Chickasaw State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 PM CDT for
west Tennessee.</instruction>
